WEBVTT

00:03.351 --> 00:05.005
[birds chirping]

00:11.489 --> 00:14.057
[car approaching]

00:15.885 --> 00:17.843
[inhales]

00:19.236 --> 00:20.368
[sighs]

00:23.762 --> 00:26.069
Okay.

00:26.113 --> 00:27.505
"Throughout his life--"

00:27.549 --> 00:30.421
No. "Throughout his career,

00:30.465 --> 00:33.946
"Frank Landau brought
Illinois Democrats together.

00:33.990 --> 00:37.124
"During the Bush years,
the rise of extremism.

00:37.167 --> 00:40.040
And now he's brought us
together one last time."

00:42.085 --> 00:43.304
Was that a grimace?

00:44.522 --> 00:45.915
No.

00:45.958 --> 00:48.004
It looked like you winced.

00:48.048 --> 00:50.659
No. A tear in my eye.

00:52.704 --> 00:54.750
You really
didn't have to do this.

00:54.793 --> 00:57.231
I'm home for two weeks, I'm
going to spend it with my wife.

00:59.407 --> 01:02.323
I will find you a drink
just as soon as we get there.

01:02.366 --> 01:03.672
Don't worry about it.

01:03.715 --> 01:04.977
I'm not going to say a word.

01:05.021 --> 01:06.066
Keep going.

01:07.893 --> 01:10.766
"On issues
like Roe v. Wadeand...

01:10.809 --> 01:12.985
"the NRA,

01:13.029 --> 01:16.424
Frank always had
his heart in the right place."

01:16.467 --> 01:17.773
-[phone dings]
-"Frank..."

01:28.784 --> 01:29.872
Who was that?

01:29.915 --> 01:30.960
Mm.

01:31.003 --> 01:32.788
Nothing, it's just a client.

01:36.313 --> 01:37.793
[water burbling]

01:37.836 --> 01:39.621
[birds hooting, chirping]

01:39.664 --> 01:41.536
GPS: Please make
a U-turn when safe.

01:41.579 --> 01:42.841
He still hasn't called?
Neil Gross?

01:42.885 --> 01:44.452
No.

01:44.495 --> 01:46.497
-Do we know where he is?
-We think Fiji.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.195
But he should've
been back last Thursday.

01:48.238 --> 01:50.632
Do we think
he's found another law firm?

01:50.675 --> 01:52.416
GPS: Please make
a U-turn when safe.

01:52.460 --> 01:55.158
Well, Chumhum has
no outstanding litigation,

01:55.202 --> 01:57.160
so my guess
is he's playing the field.

01:57.204 --> 01:59.162
He'll be
at the memorial, right?

01:59.206 --> 02:00.555
Frank Landau's
widow invited him.

02:00.598 --> 02:02.034
All right, so,
let's just corner him

02:02.078 --> 02:03.993
and make our last pitch.

02:04.036 --> 02:05.168
GPS:
Please make a U-turn...

02:05.212 --> 02:06.430
No, I won't! You fucking think

02:06.474 --> 02:07.692
I'm in fucking Baltimore.

02:07.736 --> 02:09.520
My God.

02:09.564 --> 02:10.913
GPS: You have arrived.
Please park where safe.

02:10.956 --> 02:12.088
[groans]:
Okay.

02:12.132 --> 02:15.135
♪

02:15.178 --> 02:17.180
[indistinct chatter]

02:20.879 --> 02:22.925
What if we left?

02:22.968 --> 02:24.187
Right now?

02:24.231 --> 02:25.406
I mean, I made an appearance.

02:25.449 --> 02:26.581
People saw me.

02:26.624 --> 02:27.712
Well, we haven't
even gone inside.

02:27.756 --> 02:29.453
I know, but I can...

02:29.497 --> 02:31.412
I can feel
the judgment from out here.

02:31.455 --> 02:32.804
Why would they judge you?

02:32.848 --> 02:34.415
I'm a Gold.

02:34.458 --> 02:36.460
And Frank Landau's
family didn't invite my dad.

02:36.504 --> 02:38.375
They probably blame me.

02:38.419 --> 02:41.204
Blame you because an anti-Semite
wants to murder a Jew?

02:41.248 --> 02:42.684
Who said it had to make sense?

02:46.253 --> 02:48.516
Wait a minute, stand over there.

02:48.559 --> 02:50.518
-Why?
-Zev, just do it.

03:00.571 --> 03:02.182
-Oh, my God.
-ZEV: What?

03:03.705 --> 03:06.838
It's not me.
Come on, take my arm.

03:06.882 --> 03:09.972
[bagpipe music playing]

03:15.195 --> 03:16.718
Who was that?

03:16.761 --> 03:19.329
-Marissa.
-No, the guy.

03:19.373 --> 03:21.897
JAY:
I don't know. Her boyfriend?

03:22.898 --> 03:25.422
So, is he here?

03:25.466 --> 03:26.771
Neil Gross?

03:26.815 --> 03:28.817
No, not yet.
His second-in-command is.

03:28.860 --> 03:30.166
Todd.

03:30.210 --> 03:32.124
There are two other firms
on the hunt.

03:32.168 --> 03:33.213
Colvin & Marcy.

03:33.256 --> 03:34.257
Oh, I know them. Smaller.

03:34.301 --> 03:35.780
And Russell Carton & Associates.

03:35.824 --> 03:37.695
-Oh, that's a good one.
-LIZ: Anything else?

03:37.739 --> 03:40.263
Gross is buying up
land in Puerto Rico.

03:40.307 --> 03:41.873
-Why?
-JAY: No idea.

03:41.917 --> 03:43.353
Okay, all right,
so, when we see him,

03:43.397 --> 03:45.399
let's just all text each other.
Okay?

03:45.442 --> 03:47.270
How long do we have to stay?

03:47.314 --> 03:48.750
Memorials not your scene?

03:48.793 --> 03:50.491
Small talk is not my scene.

03:50.534 --> 03:52.275
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

03:52.319 --> 03:54.321
Want me to rescue
your boyfriend?

03:54.364 --> 03:56.279
He's not my boyfriend.
He's my Krav Maga instructor.

03:56.323 --> 03:57.846
Sure.

03:57.889 --> 04:01.589
Hey, Zev? Your fiancée
wants to have a word.

04:02.807 --> 04:04.505
Were you getting lonely, "dear"?

04:04.548 --> 04:06.550
She wanted a drink.

04:06.594 --> 04:08.552
You really
come alive at memorials, huh?

04:08.596 --> 04:10.511
It's when I'm happiest.

04:10.554 --> 04:11.903
I'm grabbing a drink.
Want anything?

04:11.947 --> 04:13.165
An Old Fashioned.

04:13.209 --> 04:14.428
Tell me if you see Ben-Baruch.

04:14.471 --> 04:16.734
-He's coming here?
-A long story.

04:18.867 --> 04:21.391
So we're getting married, huh?

04:21.435 --> 04:25.177
In Carmen's mind. She's
particularly melodramatic today.

04:27.310 --> 04:28.877
JAY:
No drinks?

04:28.920 --> 04:30.444
Then you have a few minutes.

04:30.487 --> 04:31.575
For what?

04:35.362 --> 04:36.493
Jay, what are we doing?

04:36.537 --> 04:37.799
You don't have to do this,

04:37.842 --> 04:38.800
but there are people
who need us.

04:38.843 --> 04:40.410
What are we talking about?

04:40.454 --> 04:42.325
Something bigger than all this.

04:42.369 --> 04:43.631
CARMEN:
Who's that?

04:43.674 --> 04:45.589
JAY:
A way to help our community.

04:45.633 --> 04:48.505
Jay, I'm not you.
You want to better the world.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.202
I want to better my life.

04:51.813 --> 04:52.901
They have money.

04:56.078 --> 04:58.298
RI'CHARD: It's not just that
we want Puerto Rico's law school

04:58.341 --> 05:00.387
to have national stature,
we also want students

05:00.430 --> 05:02.867
and faculty
engaged in the community...

05:02.911 --> 05:04.869
Look, nothing's
been decided yet.

05:04.913 --> 05:06.567
We're still considering you.

05:06.610 --> 05:08.220
Do you know
when Neil is arriving?

05:08.264 --> 05:10.266
Unfortunately, he's
been called away to Beijing.

05:11.659 --> 05:13.138
We'll arrange a call.

05:17.534 --> 05:18.709
Fuck.

05:19.754 --> 05:21.059
Do you find swearing helps?

05:21.103 --> 05:22.539
All the fuckin' time.

05:22.583 --> 05:24.106
We need to get him
on the phone.

05:24.149 --> 05:26.151
I've been trying.
He won't pick up.

05:26.195 --> 05:28.284
How many will we lose
if we lose Chumhum?

05:28.328 --> 05:30.721
-Half of tech. 30 clients.
-[bell ringing]

05:30.765 --> 05:32.419
More.

05:32.462 --> 05:34.508
We're about to begin.
Please move into the Great Room.

05:36.118 --> 05:38.120
[prisoners shouting]

05:38.163 --> 05:39.730
BUCK: I know my rights!
You have no idea...

05:39.774 --> 05:42.603
-GUARD: Hey.
-Hey! Hey.

05:42.646 --> 05:45.693
I want my lawyer. I know
my rights and I want my lawyer!

05:45.736 --> 05:47.129
Stand up.
Back against the door.

05:47.172 --> 05:48.348
Fuck you.

05:48.391 --> 05:50.393
Fine.
You don't want your call.

05:50.437 --> 05:53.048
Wait, wait, wait.
Get back here.

05:53.091 --> 05:54.789
Hands.
Show me hands.

05:57.313 --> 06:00.882
How am I gonna make
my call with no hands, huh?

06:00.925 --> 06:02.971
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

06:04.668 --> 06:07.062
[lock buzzing]

06:11.022 --> 06:13.460
I know my rights. You're
not holding my receiver for me.

06:13.503 --> 06:15.375
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Shut up.

06:15.418 --> 06:17.768
You have no fucking idea
who you're dealing with.

06:27.996 --> 06:30.259
Attorney/client privilege.

06:30.302 --> 06:31.739
Back the fuck off!

06:36.221 --> 06:38.267
[P.A. announcements continue]

06:40.791 --> 06:42.793
♪

06:45.013 --> 06:47.494
[siren sound effects playing]

06:53.978 --> 06:55.545
Good job.

06:58.505 --> 07:00.332
[beeping]

07:02.596 --> 07:05.599
♪

07:05.642 --> 07:07.427
[modem beeping]

07:16.174 --> 07:17.567
Stanley, Berkeley & Associates.

07:17.611 --> 07:18.960
Mid-level firm.

07:19.003 --> 07:21.397
Five partners.
Mostly criminal defense.

07:21.441 --> 07:22.746
In The Loop. White shoe.

07:22.790 --> 07:23.878
What she said.

07:25.270 --> 07:28.012
[busy chatter
sound effect playing]

07:28.056 --> 07:30.493
Stanley, Berkeley & Associates.
How may I help you?

07:30.537 --> 07:32.495
John Lincoln. Right away.

07:32.539 --> 07:34.149
May I tell him
what this is regarding?

07:34.192 --> 07:37.544
No, you may not. Just
tell him it's Buck, squad eight.

07:37.587 --> 07:39.284
One moment.

07:39.328 --> 07:42.984
You're a new-hire.
John Lincoln is at lunch.

07:43.027 --> 07:44.638
He asked you to just handle
the prep for the bond hearing

07:44.681 --> 07:45.943
before he gets there.

07:45.987 --> 07:47.771
But if he's
a white supremacist,

07:47.815 --> 07:49.817
is he gonna want
to work with someone Black?

07:49.860 --> 07:50.992
-No.
-CARMEN: So...?

07:51.035 --> 07:52.080
It's up to you.

07:53.081 --> 07:56.737
Not yet.
You gotta make him sweat.

07:56.780 --> 07:59.261
Your name is Carmen Alden.
Say it.

07:59.304 --> 08:00.697
-I'm Carmen Alden.
-And you're a bit harried.

08:00.741 --> 08:03.047
John keeps shoving
too many cases at you.

08:03.091 --> 08:05.485
You're eating
a salad in the conference room

08:05.528 --> 08:07.182
with other associates.

08:07.225 --> 08:08.400
This is what it looks like.

08:08.444 --> 08:09.271
I know.
I interviewed there.

08:09.314 --> 08:10.490
They didn't want me.

08:10.533 --> 08:12.100
Good.
Use your memory of it.

08:12.143 --> 08:14.232
You're out
the door to meet him now.

08:14.276 --> 08:15.799
Walk as you talk. Okay?

08:17.148 --> 08:20.325
This is Carmen Alden.
Who is this please?

08:20.369 --> 08:21.588
Who are you?

08:21.631 --> 08:23.503
CARMEN:
Mr. Lincoln's associate.

08:23.546 --> 08:25.156
He's at lunch, but he asked me
to prep for your bond hearing.

08:25.200 --> 08:26.810
No, I don't know you, lady.

08:26.854 --> 08:29.247
That's okay. Mr. Lincoln
briefed me on your needs.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.859
This is bullshit.
He's supposed to be available.

08:31.902 --> 08:33.425
CARMEN:
And he will be.

08:33.469 --> 08:35.079
But Mr. Lincoln knows
that if we don't jump

08:35.123 --> 08:36.646
on this right now,
the police will be thrilled

08:36.690 --> 08:38.343
to keep you
in there over the weekend.

08:38.387 --> 08:40.563
You unfortunately
chose a Friday to get arrested.

08:40.607 --> 08:42.739
Get me someone else there.
I wanna talk to somebody else.

08:42.783 --> 08:44.480
CARMEN: Look, I don't
have time for this.

08:44.524 --> 08:47.222
Okay? I have other cases.
Call again on Monday.

08:47.265 --> 08:48.571
No, no, wait, wait.

08:48.615 --> 08:49.964
I need out today.

08:50.007 --> 08:51.661
Understood.
I'm 20 minutes away.

08:51.705 --> 08:53.794
If you get any harassment,

08:53.837 --> 08:55.447
tell the guard on duty that
"John has your number."

08:55.491 --> 08:57.406
Now sit tight.
And don't tell anybody anything.

08:57.449 --> 08:58.581
You understand?

08:58.625 --> 09:00.017
Keep your
fuckin' mouth shut.

09:02.324 --> 09:04.456
-RENETTA: Okay.
-I believed you.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.849
-What's your size?
-My size?

09:05.893 --> 09:07.459
RENETTA:
Clothes. Your size?

09:07.503 --> 09:09.853
-Six.
-We need you in work attire.

09:09.897 --> 09:13.335
No. Let's play it like
I was going to a funeral.

09:13.378 --> 09:14.989
RANDY: I think work attire
would be better...

09:15.032 --> 09:17.426
Actually, she's right.
Let's stick closer to the truth.

09:17.469 --> 09:19.820
Okay, we've got 20 minutes
to prep you. Let's go.

09:19.863 --> 09:21.996
[bagpipe music playing]

09:32.006 --> 09:33.355
Good afternoon.

09:33.398 --> 09:35.531
If you don't recognize me...

09:35.575 --> 09:37.141
[feedback squeals,
microphone cuts out]

09:37.185 --> 09:38.578
Uh, hello?

09:40.057 --> 09:43.191
Good afternoon.
If you don't recognize me,

09:43.234 --> 09:45.628
I'm the new head of the DNC,
I'm Johnny Elfman.

09:45.672 --> 09:48.762
And this is how the midterms
are going for me, so far.

09:48.805 --> 09:50.328
[laughter]

09:50.372 --> 09:53.244
Some stairs. In Georgia.
I fell down the stairs.

09:53.288 --> 09:57.640
Time has not been very good
to the Democratic Party.

09:57.684 --> 09:59.773
The Supreme Court.
Republican obstructionism.

09:59.816 --> 10:01.209
School shootings.

10:01.252 --> 10:04.038
There are more children
killed every year

10:04.081 --> 10:06.997
from firearms than cancer,
and the NRA still doesn't care.

10:07.041 --> 10:11.088
And now here we are,
gathered today over the loss

10:11.132 --> 10:14.222
of Frank Landau,
a man who truly cared--

10:14.265 --> 10:15.702
-[feedback squeals]
-Whoa.

10:18.618 --> 10:19.880
A man who truly cared.

10:21.359 --> 10:23.144
-We'll be hearing from friends--
-[microphone cuts out]

10:24.972 --> 10:26.800
[sighs]

10:26.843 --> 10:29.716
We'll be hearing from friends
and admirers of Frank.

10:29.759 --> 10:32.893
So, please,
wipe away those tears,

10:32.936 --> 10:35.243
and let's remember
what Frank always told us.

10:35.286 --> 10:36.505
Who is he?

10:36.548 --> 10:38.376
A client.

10:38.420 --> 10:40.161
ZEV: I recognize him
from Tel Aviv.

10:40.204 --> 10:42.380
-He's a criminal.
-Okay.

10:42.424 --> 10:44.731
Let's not get
too confrontational, hubby.

10:44.774 --> 10:47.647
After graduating
from Yale, I struggled

10:47.690 --> 10:49.779
with nepotism
and small-mindedness.

10:49.823 --> 10:52.869
And I'll never forget the
words that Frank offered me:

10:52.913 --> 10:56.046
"You can beat anyone
if you put your mind to it."

10:56.090 --> 10:59.528
And that's all I needed
to become the top lawyer in D.C.

10:59.571 --> 11:02.966
And one of the 30
most eligible bachelors

11:03.010 --> 11:04.707
under 40 in the D.C. area,

11:04.751 --> 11:07.014
according
to Law Lifemagazine.

11:07.057 --> 11:10.147
Frank used to say to me,
"Dan, I know that you,

11:10.191 --> 11:12.802
Daniel Grey,
are the future of this party."

11:13.803 --> 11:17.111
That was Frank.
He had that kind of vision.

11:17.154 --> 11:19.113
The best way to talk
about Frank is to talk

11:19.156 --> 11:23.726
about myself and the successes
we had at the AFL-CIO.

11:23.770 --> 11:26.424
When Frank chose me to lead
those negotiations,

11:26.468 --> 11:28.949
he knew he chose a leader.

11:28.992 --> 11:31.125
And frankly,
no pun intended,

11:31.168 --> 11:32.909
lead, I did.

11:35.042 --> 11:38.306
TV REPORTER: In our breaking
headline story this hour,

11:38.349 --> 11:40.874
reporting live
from Washington, D.C.

11:40.917 --> 11:43.180
Although information
is not yet available,

11:43.224 --> 11:45.530
in a second apparent leak,

11:45.574 --> 11:47.663
the conservative majority
of the Supreme Court

11:47.707 --> 11:50.666
decided
to overturn gay marriage.

11:50.710 --> 11:53.277
In what appears to be
an initial draft decision,

11:53.321 --> 11:56.019
the Court assets
that gay marriage

11:56.063 --> 11:57.934
does not enjoy
privacy protection.

11:57.978 --> 12:00.197
Oh, Jesus.

12:00.241 --> 12:01.851
TV REPORTER: We have been
unable to confirm

12:01.895 --> 12:03.331
this leaked document's
authenticity, but the...

12:03.374 --> 12:05.246
We're opening early.

12:05.289 --> 12:07.814
TV REPORTER: "Even though
this Court's earlier ruling

12:07.857 --> 12:10.207
"on abortion concluded
it would have no impact

12:10.251 --> 12:12.906
on gay marriage,
we changed our minds."

12:12.949 --> 12:15.473
The draft opinion
cited Creetin Spencer,

12:15.517 --> 12:18.781
an 11th century
Thessaloniki judge who wrote:

12:18.825 --> 12:22.785
"Smote me not thy heed,
sleepeth not with thy brethren."

12:22.829 --> 12:24.569
After the Supreme Court's
decision

12:24.613 --> 12:26.354
to reverseRoe v. Wade...

12:26.397 --> 12:28.008
There's not enough
whiskey in the world.

12:28.051 --> 12:29.661
TV REPORTER:
...to offer a preview

12:29.705 --> 12:31.489
of the Court's
potential rulings

12:31.533 --> 12:33.709
suggesting the right-winged
controlled Court

12:33.753 --> 12:36.799
may return to the issues
of contraception access

12:36.843 --> 12:38.670
and marriage equality.

12:38.714 --> 12:40.672
This one hurts.

12:42.022 --> 12:44.111
-[phones dinging]
-Taken from us too young,

12:44.154 --> 12:46.243
he hadn't
even turned 70 yet.

12:47.810 --> 12:50.508
I believe in the future
of the Democratic Party.

12:50.552 --> 12:54.164
Please remember
to turn off your phones.

12:54.208 --> 12:56.123
What's going on?

12:57.211 --> 12:58.473
Gay marriage.

12:58.516 --> 13:00.518
ELIZABETH:
I believe in tomorrow.

13:00.562 --> 13:03.086
I believe we're coming back.

13:05.610 --> 13:07.177
MINISTER:
And now for our final speaker.

13:07.221 --> 13:11.181
A friend who worked
with Frank for two decades.

13:11.225 --> 13:13.357
Ms. Diane Lockhart.

13:15.359 --> 13:16.796
Diane Lockhart.

13:19.189 --> 13:20.451
Is she here?

13:20.495 --> 13:21.670
[TV newscast playing]

13:21.713 --> 13:25.152
Diane.
Your speech. Come on.

13:28.764 --> 13:30.070
You okay?

13:31.288 --> 13:32.246
Peachy.

13:32.289 --> 13:34.857
♪

13:47.391 --> 13:48.479
Well.

13:50.351 --> 13:52.657
Hello.
Here we all are.

13:52.701 --> 13:54.921
Every Democrat
that tried to do something.

13:56.792 --> 13:59.403
We came to bury
Frank Landau, not to praise him.

14:00.665 --> 14:02.232
And it looks
like we're gonna bury

14:02.276 --> 14:04.321
the Democratic Party instead.

14:04.365 --> 14:06.715
Because let's face it, folks.

14:06.758 --> 14:08.412
We're fucked.

14:13.243 --> 14:14.810
Thank you for sharing.

14:14.854 --> 14:18.205
If we could all bow our heads.

14:18.248 --> 14:20.294
♪

14:27.431 --> 14:31.435
Here's to democracy
and your life's work.

14:33.307 --> 14:34.874
NEIL:
I liked your speech.

14:38.138 --> 14:39.617
What?

14:39.661 --> 14:41.532
I saw your speech. I liked it.

14:43.317 --> 14:45.710
-All 30 words?
-40.

14:45.754 --> 14:48.931
I tend to count words
in my mind. I'm not proud of it.

14:50.628 --> 14:52.630
I thought you
weren't coming, Mr. Gross.

14:52.674 --> 14:54.676
I wasn't.
But I had a dream last night.

14:54.719 --> 14:56.286
About what?

14:56.330 --> 14:57.984
It was about
the end of the world.

