and the ones we've lost?

29:43.172 --> 29:44.826
I mean, Jesus Christ,

29:44.870 --> 29:46.393
this country
is in real fucking trouble

29:46.436 --> 29:47.873
and you want
to play king for a day?

29:47.916 --> 29:49.396
Fuck off.

29:50.397 --> 29:52.834
I'm buying Fox News.

30:00.668 --> 30:02.844
[lock buzzing]

30:04.541 --> 30:07.196
Oh, come on,
is this necessary?

30:07.240 --> 30:09.329
Hey, gently. Gently.

30:09.372 --> 30:11.331
Jesus, knock off
this Homan Square shit.

30:11.374 --> 30:13.202
Come on, take the hood off,
asshole!

30:13.246 --> 30:15.030
You try that
again with him

30:15.074 --> 30:16.553
and you'll
have a lawsuit so fast,

30:16.597 --> 30:17.641
you won't know what hit you.

30:17.685 --> 30:20.035
Now get the fuck out.

30:20.079 --> 30:21.210
You, too.

30:21.254 --> 30:22.821
[door closes]

30:22.864 --> 30:24.779
Manners.

30:24.823 --> 30:28.522
Well, I'm Carmen Alden.
We talked on the phone.

30:28.565 --> 30:30.480
Your bond hearing
should be in a few hours.

30:30.524 --> 30:33.701
But I just need to get
a few details straight.

30:33.744 --> 30:36.008
Were you driving
the van for someone else?

30:39.968 --> 30:41.927
You know, it would help
our bail argument

30:41.970 --> 30:44.190
if the fertilizer
wasn't yours.

30:44.233 --> 30:48.455
I can't tell you how to testify,
but again, I can probably

30:48.498 --> 30:51.850
get you out if the van
belonged to someone else.

30:56.028 --> 30:58.465
Are we having
some problems here, Mr. Burns?

30:58.508 --> 31:00.684
I'm not talking to you.

31:00.728 --> 31:01.990
That will make this difficult.

31:02.034 --> 31:03.862
You're fuckin' Black.

31:06.038 --> 31:08.040
Where's Big John?
Where's Chuck?

31:08.083 --> 31:10.303
Which Chuck?
'Cause I've got three of them.

31:10.346 --> 31:14.524
BUCK: Fuck you. Go back
to the shithole you came from.

31:15.786 --> 31:18.485
Fine by me.
I have other things to do.

31:20.052 --> 31:22.924
But did you think about it,
really?

31:22.968 --> 31:24.534
Did you think
there might be a reason

31:24.578 --> 31:26.972
that Mr. Lincoln
sent you a Black lawyer?

31:27.015 --> 31:29.409
It's Chicago.

31:29.452 --> 31:33.630
The courts, they just kiss the
ass of a Black lawyer like me.

31:33.674 --> 31:35.545
And you're going
in front of Judge Gellar,

31:35.589 --> 31:40.289
he's one of the angriest BLM
ass-lickers on the bench.

31:40.333 --> 31:41.987
And you think
John Lincoln argues for you,

31:42.030 --> 31:43.945
you'll get out on bail?

31:43.989 --> 31:45.860
Or this face?

31:45.904 --> 31:47.993
Okay.

31:48.036 --> 31:49.385
Have fun
in jail over the weekend.

31:49.429 --> 31:52.040
But if you
end up in Homan Square...

31:52.084 --> 31:53.650
-[lock buzzing]
-don't cry on my shoulder.

31:53.694 --> 31:54.913
We're done.

31:58.394 --> 32:00.266
Why would you defend me?!

32:08.100 --> 32:09.536
Because, why do you think?

32:11.668 --> 32:16.021
Money. I'd defend
the devil for money.

32:16.064 --> 32:18.762
I have defended
the devil for money.

32:18.806 --> 32:20.155
Do you know Oscar Rivi?

32:20.199 --> 32:22.505
Top crystal dealer
in Chicago?

32:22.549 --> 32:23.942
I got him off.

32:23.985 --> 32:27.554
And do you know why?
For money.

32:27.597 --> 32:30.861
Now, I don't care who
he hurt or who he fucked.

32:30.905 --> 32:35.127
It could have been my mother.
But my job is to get him off.

32:35.170 --> 32:37.868
My job is to get you off.

32:37.912 --> 32:40.610
You know, I grew up
with a father who only cared

32:40.654 --> 32:44.701
about causes,
and he bankrupted us

32:44.745 --> 32:47.574
with his marches
and his door knocking.

32:47.617 --> 32:49.968
And I got dragged
around from door to door

32:50.011 --> 32:52.318
for Jesse Jackson
and all that crap.

32:52.361 --> 32:53.710
Is this all true?

32:53.754 --> 32:54.842
I don't know.

32:54.885 --> 32:56.452
Doesn't matter.

32:56.496 --> 32:58.411
You see,
the point isn't the end.

32:59.455 --> 33:01.022
The point is the expertise.

33:01.066 --> 33:02.545
The point is winning.

33:03.546 --> 33:06.549
That is why I'm here
because I want to win.

33:07.724 --> 33:10.553
But if you don't care, fuck you.

33:12.251 --> 33:15.994
Either way,
I'm getting the money.

33:17.038 --> 33:18.126
Guard?

33:19.562 --> 33:21.129
[lock buzzing]

33:21.173 --> 33:22.348
We're done, Buck.

33:26.091 --> 33:27.788
BUCK:
Wait!

33:27.831 --> 33:29.485
Wait.

33:35.926 --> 33:37.711
Okay. I don't know
if I trust this guy.

33:37.754 --> 33:39.278
Come back in ten minutes.

33:39.321 --> 33:41.845
Don't you dare listen
by the door, you asshole.

33:41.889 --> 33:43.456
I know how you work.

33:43.499 --> 33:44.892
[door closes]

33:44.935 --> 33:48.069
Okay, help me out.

33:48.113 --> 33:49.897
I need details
for the bond hearing.

33:54.119 --> 33:56.077
How do you buy Fox News?

33:56.121 --> 33:57.513
With money.

33:57.557 --> 33:59.167
How much?

33:59.211 --> 34:01.300
It's current worth
is $21 billion.

34:01.343 --> 34:03.780
I can become a majority
owner with $15 billion.

34:03.824 --> 34:06.044
-And you'd be willing
to do that?
-Yes.

34:06.087 --> 34:07.567
The Republicans
will just find some other

34:07.610 --> 34:09.134
network to call their own.

34:09.177 --> 34:11.179
Well, sure, if you turned
Fox Democrat overnight.

34:11.223 --> 34:12.789
But you don't do that.

34:12.833 --> 34:15.401
The thought is to start
curbing its excesses.

34:15.444 --> 34:18.012
To make Fox more reliably
conservative-- not radical.

34:18.056 --> 34:21.102
Still, the nuts will just
flee someplace else.

34:21.146 --> 34:24.105
Maybe. There's a certain
period of whack-a-mole.

34:24.149 --> 34:25.759
Always is.

34:25.802 --> 34:29.023
Mr. Gross has promised
a massive investment in the DNC.

34:29.067 --> 34:32.287
12 years,
three presidential cycles.

34:32.331 --> 34:34.376
And he's already heavily
investing in Puerto Rico.

34:34.420 --> 34:36.465
-The 51st state?
-Of course.

34:36.509 --> 34:38.641
A Democratic one.

34:38.685 --> 34:41.514
And how will you work
with the Biden administration?

34:45.257 --> 34:51.524
I won't. He served you well
in 2020 but the brand is tired.

34:51.567 --> 34:54.266
You need someone fresh,
the stakes are too high.

34:54.309 --> 34:56.442
-Okay, I see
where this is going.
-NEIL: You do?

34:56.485 --> 34:59.009
Yeah. You think you're
the next Michael Bloomberg,

34:59.053 --> 35:01.011
a guy with too much money
who thinks he's the answer.

35:01.055 --> 35:03.101
-Are you done?
-No. I'm not, thank you.

35:03.144 --> 35:04.885
Why don't you go start your
own political party, Mr. Gross.

35:06.582 --> 35:08.932
I know about
your brother's mistress.

35:11.718 --> 35:13.285
What the hell
are you talking about?

35:13.328 --> 35:15.417
You're the king
of oppo research.

35:15.461 --> 35:17.593
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

35:18.812 --> 35:20.161
Do you know what
Republican candidate

35:20.205 --> 35:22.946
killed a classmate in 1986?

35:22.990 --> 35:24.165
I do.

35:24.209 --> 35:26.298
You know
what Supreme Court justice

35:26.341 --> 35:28.648
has a child porn problem?
I do.

35:30.345 --> 35:32.739
The Democratic Party
doesn't play this game.

35:32.782 --> 35:36.046
Oh, course it does. And if it
doesn't, it sure needs to start.

35:37.091 --> 35:38.701
Do you know how
I know all your secrets?

35:38.745 --> 35:40.616
I own Chumhum.

35:40.660 --> 35:45.186
We have 2.9 billion
active users every month.

35:45.230 --> 35:47.319
I have records
of all their interests,

35:47.362 --> 35:49.756
and their biases,
their secrets.

35:49.799 --> 35:52.541
And, for the right cause,
I'm willing to use them.

35:53.847 --> 35:56.284
-You're a dangerous man.
-Oh, yes.

35:56.328 --> 35:57.981
Good thing I have a friend
over in the Justice Department.

35:58.025 --> 35:59.113
Maybe I'll give him a call.

35:59.157 --> 36:01.333
Oh-- All right, go for it.

36:01.376 --> 36:03.291
I'm sure Merrick Garland
will hop right on it.

36:03.335 --> 36:06.990
You know, I don't think you
realize, Mr. Elfperson,

36:07.034 --> 36:09.384
the Trump years have turned
everything on its head.

36:09.428 --> 36:11.299
And the Democratic Party
is still acting like we're

36:11.343 --> 36:13.823
all sitting around sipping
toddies with Tip O'Neill.

36:13.867 --> 36:17.827
Just one
big happy political family.

36:17.871 --> 36:20.003
Diane, we need to talk.

36:23.964 --> 36:26.445
[crickets chirping]

36:28.447 --> 36:31.580
I think he's going to say "no."
And that's why I need you.

36:32.625 --> 36:33.626
Need me? To what?

36:33.669 --> 36:35.889
To run the Democratic Party.

36:35.932 --> 36:38.674
Yeah, my backup plan
is a hostile takeover.

36:38.718 --> 36:42.287
Kick Elf-guy out,
and put you in.

36:42.330 --> 36:45.159
I-- Sorry, I don't, I don't
know what to say to that.

36:45.203 --> 36:47.988
It doesn't really matter.
You'll eventually say "yes."

36:48.031 --> 36:50.382
And then you will need
to talk to your husband.

36:50.425 --> 36:52.645
-My husband?
-Yeah. You need to
keep him in line.

36:52.688 --> 36:55.517
Or, uh, divorce him.

36:55.561 --> 36:57.911
-Excuse me?
-The interests of the party

36:57.954 --> 36:59.956
supersede any family concerns.

37:00.000 --> 37:02.350
Just tell him you can't
see another school shooting

37:02.394 --> 37:05.310
without shooting yourself.

37:05.353 --> 37:08.443
Tell him his work
with the NRA disgusts you.

37:08.487 --> 37:10.532
Oh, look,
here's his answer now.

37:11.620 --> 37:14.406
I want you
to step in for Elfman, Diane.

37:14.449 --> 37:16.756
And you'll need
to deal with your husband first.

37:19.585 --> 37:22.762
-Well?
-No. I don't trust you.

37:22.805 --> 37:24.807
NEIL:
Is that your final answer?

37:24.851 --> 37:26.983
We can't just run you, sir.
We have a seniority system.

37:27.027 --> 37:28.681
We have Biden.
We have Kamala. We have Bernie.

37:28.724 --> 37:30.639
And they'll all lose.

37:30.683 --> 37:32.337
It's better
than some tech billionaire.

37:32.380 --> 37:33.947
[scoffs]

37:33.990 --> 37:35.470
I'm not talking about myself.

37:35.514 --> 37:36.819
God, no.

37:37.951 --> 37:39.300
I have a candidate.

37:39.344 --> 37:41.389
One who is sounding out
both parties.

37:41.433 --> 37:44.305
He's dropped everything,
he's on his way here right now.

37:44.349 --> 37:46.351
Who? Who is it?
Who's on his way here?

37:48.004 --> 37:49.267
Dwayne Johnson.

37:50.790 --> 37:52.313
The Rock.

37:53.967 --> 37:55.185
Like Peter.

38:02.715 --> 38:04.107
Are you serious?

38:04.151 --> 38:06.501
Like a fucking heart attack.

38:06.545 --> 38:09.635
Upon this rock,
I'll build my party.

38:09.678 --> 38:12.290
♪

38:20.298 --> 38:22.125
I'll get the bail set.
But don't talk to anyone here.

38:22.169 --> 38:24.476
Anyone in the cell next to you
is just trying to fuck you.

38:24.519 --> 38:26.739
I need Chuck
to help me with my girlfriend.

38:26.782 --> 38:29.785
If she doesn't get rent
this week she'll be kicked out.

38:29.829 --> 38:33.049
You tell Chuck Pearce
that if he doesn't help,

38:33.093 --> 38:34.312
I'm turning on him.

38:34.355 --> 38:37.576
Understood. Get ready.

38:37.619 --> 38:39.360
The hearing
should be in an hour.

38:39.404 --> 38:41.623
And you'll be out of here.

38:41.667 --> 38:43.538
[lock buzzing]

38:43.582 --> 38:45.801
♪

38:54.244 --> 38:56.290
Chuck Pearce
runs oil refineries

38:56.334 --> 38:58.901
in Oklahoma and is the chief
financier of the Michigan Army.

38:58.945 --> 39:00.773
Senator Kiersten Judd
of Mississippi

39:00.816 --> 39:02.601
is their second largest donor.

39:02.644 --> 39:03.863
Hmm.

39:03.906 --> 39:06.213
Good work, Carmen.
Good leads.

39:06.256 --> 39:07.562
Where are we, Jay?

39:07.606 --> 39:09.738
Done. Their bank
accounts are drained.

39:09.782 --> 39:11.566
Good. The Michigan Army
officially bankrupt.

39:11.610 --> 39:13.263
Let's get rid of these guys.

39:13.307 --> 39:14.961
BUCK: What the fuck
are you doing?

39:15.004 --> 39:17.398
What the--?
What the fuck? Come on!

39:17.442 --> 39:18.878
What are you doing?
Where are we going?

39:18.921 --> 39:19.966
Who's that?

39:21.663 --> 39:23.012
Frank Landau's assassin.

39:23.056 --> 39:24.666
BUCK:
Where are you taking me?

39:24.710 --> 39:26.973
You can't do this without me
talking to my lawyer.

39:27.016 --> 39:28.801
MAN: Where are we going?
Hold on. Stop. Stop.

39:28.844 --> 39:30.672
[Buck shouting indistinctly]

39:32.805 --> 39:35.285
-Where are they going?
-Antarctica.

39:35.329 --> 39:37.549
-Is that code or something?
-Nope.

39:37.592 --> 39:39.681
We have a private jet
bound for Antarctica.

39:39.725 --> 39:41.596
Some of our donors
built a facility there,

39:41.640 --> 39:44.120
with private cells
for white supremacists.

39:44.164 --> 39:46.166
Every day
they can look out on white.

40:03.401 --> 40:06.708
-Is he gonna get out?
-No, you go to him.

40:06.752 --> 40:08.884
Oh, my God.
Is this guy serious or not?

40:08.928 --> 40:11.887
This is The Rock. How did
you think this was gonna work?

40:11.931 --> 40:13.933
Trump came down an escalator.

40:13.976 --> 40:15.500
Why can't
he roll up in an Escalade?

40:15.543 --> 40:17.371
JOHNNY:
Because we're not them.

40:17.415 --> 40:18.851
And when we try
to be them, it backfires.

40:18.894 --> 40:20.766
Look, don't waste
his time, okay?

40:20.809 --> 40:23.072
Either take it seriously
or we just drop the whole thing.

40:23.116 --> 40:26.554
Fine. Can't wait
to hear his thoughts on trade.

40:28.513 --> 40:29.470
RI'CHARD:
Now what?

40:29.514 --> 40:32.038
Now we just wait.

40:32.081 --> 40:35.781
And now, Diane,
you have some thinking to do.

40:41.395 --> 40:42.614
What was that about?

40:44.354 --> 40:49.708
As a backup plan, Neil wants
me to run the Democratic Party.

40:49.751 --> 40:51.927
[both laughing]

40:53.494 --> 40:55.191
Are you-- You're kidding?

40:55.235 --> 40:57.106
Mm-mm.

40:57.150 --> 40:58.934
Is that something
you would even want to do?

40:58.978 --> 41:00.675
I honestly don't know.

41:02.155 --> 41:04.636
But we need a radical change.

41:04.679 --> 41:07.029
And Neil has
the resources, the contacts,

41:07.073 --> 41:09.118
and the, and the guts to do it.

41:11.033 --> 41:12.992
And despite everything
that's happened, I...

41:14.210 --> 41:16.256
I still want to believe
in this country.

41:17.387 --> 41:20.390
Oh, God, I still want to
fight for it. I really do.

41:20.434 --> 41:24.438
Well, I...
I'd be sad to see you go.

41:24.482 --> 41:27.180
Come on, Liz.
You don't need me.

41:27.223 --> 41:28.921
Except as a drinking partner.

41:28.964 --> 41:31.532
[both laughing]

41:31.576 --> 41:33.229
-Besides, you have Ri'Chard.
-Yeah.

41:33.273 --> 41:34.927
He's...

41:34.970 --> 41:37.669
he's turning out to be a
better partner than I imagined.

41:38.670 --> 41:40.889
I don't know, maybe...
maybe we can

41:40.933 --> 41:43.196
become the largest firm
in the world.

41:43.239 --> 41:46.982
Oh, if I run the DNC,
you'll always have our business.

41:47.026 --> 41:50.159
This is either the stupidest
night of our lives...

41:50.203 --> 41:51.509
Or the best.

41:55.556 --> 41:57.863
I'm feeling it.

41:57.906 --> 41:59.604
What?

41:59.647 --> 42:01.519
That most dangerous feeling...

42:03.216 --> 42:04.217
Hope.

42:05.261 --> 42:07.394
Yeah. There's only one problem.

42:07.437 --> 42:08.569
What?

42:08.613 --> 42:11.964
He wants me to figure out Kurt.

42:14.488 --> 42:15.924
The NRA.

42:15.968 --> 42:17.317
Oh, God.

42:17.360 --> 42:20.712
Right.
That's awkward.

42:20.755 --> 42:23.018
In more ways
than you can imagine.

42:33.115 --> 42:35.117
Is he all right?

42:36.466 --> 42:39.557
♪

42:46.346 --> 42:48.653
I think we can see
a way to making this work.

42:48.696 --> 42:51.830
He had some fascinating
and inspired ideas.

42:53.919 --> 42:55.703
What happened to your crutches?

42:55.747 --> 42:58.706
Oh, he laid his hands
on my ankle.

43:01.187 --> 43:02.797
W-Where did he go?

43:02.841 --> 43:04.494
Oh, he had an appointment.

43:04.538 --> 43:06.627
NEIL:
Ah, one more thing.

43:06.671 --> 43:09.325
We need to accommodate
his shooting schedule.

43:09.369 --> 43:11.676
First he needs to tell
the Republican Party "no"

43:11.719 --> 43:15.418
and then he is signed on
to do Scorpion King 6.

43:15.462 --> 43:17.290
He wants to do both.

43:17.333 --> 43:20.119
Of course the presidency
would be in first position.

43:20.162 --> 43:23.252
♪

43:27.735 --> 43:29.215
-Hello!
-CARMEN: Hey!

43:29.258 --> 43:30.520
We have the witnesses!

43:30.564 --> 43:32.000
-You made it!
-We did.

43:32.044 --> 43:34.002
I thought
you guys were joking.

43:34.046 --> 43:35.525
-We were.
-Then we weren't.

43:35.569 --> 43:38.224
JULIUS:
All right. You kids ready?

43:38.267 --> 43:42.445
Marissa Gold,
do you take Zev Beker

43:42.489 --> 43:44.404
to be your lawfully
wedded husband?

43:44.447 --> 43:46.014
I do.

43:46.058 --> 43:48.060
Zev Beker, do you

43:48.103 --> 43:50.976
take Marissa Gold to be
your lawfully wedded wife?

43:51.019 --> 43:52.542
I do.

43:52.586 --> 43:54.762
I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

43:54.806 --> 43:56.808
[cheering]

43:56.851 --> 43:58.897
♪

44:14.042 --> 44:15.653
[phone dings]

44:22.921 --> 44:24.966
KURT:
Your client again?

44:25.010 --> 44:27.360
No. The RNC.

44:29.710 --> 44:32.234
Did you give them money
in my name?

44:32.278 --> 44:33.366
No.

44:34.628 --> 44:36.499
"Dear Mr. and Mrs. McVeigh,

44:36.543 --> 44:40.112
"Thank you very much
for your generous contribution

44:40.155 --> 44:42.070
to the Republican
National Committee."

44:42.114 --> 44:43.985
It's a form letter.

44:45.247 --> 44:47.902
They're mailing us MAGA hats.

44:47.946 --> 44:49.817
Don't say
I never gave you anything.

45:00.175 --> 45:03.526
Kurt.
This isn't working.

45:10.229 --> 45:11.534
What isn't?

45:11.578 --> 45:12.927
You and me.

45:15.495 --> 45:17.105
Why not?

45:17.149 --> 45:20.543
You know why not.
We have nothing in common.

45:20.587 --> 45:22.284
[Kurt sighs]

45:22.328 --> 45:23.938
Every time we talk,

45:23.982 --> 45:26.071
it's a minefield
of political frustrations.

45:26.114 --> 45:27.637
Not for me.

45:27.681 --> 45:29.552
Then you're a better person.

45:29.596 --> 45:33.295
Diane, I-I haven't changed.
You knew what I believed in.

45:33.339 --> 45:35.036
Yes. But the world has changed.

45:35.080 --> 45:36.951
The right wing has changed.

45:39.040 --> 45:41.173
I mean, these school shootings.

45:41.216 --> 45:44.829
I lie awake at night,
and I'm thinking

45:44.872 --> 45:47.179
I can't believe
what you believe in.

45:49.485 --> 45:52.184
You seem so sane,
and yet these people...

45:53.359 --> 45:57.450
Ted Cruz.
Marjorie Taylor Greene. Boebert.

45:57.493 --> 45:59.931
Diane, we've always stayed away
from all that kind of stuff.

45:59.974 --> 46:04.326
Well, I can't anymore.
I-- I just can't.

46:08.113 --> 46:09.375
Have you met someone?

46:11.769 --> 46:14.293
No. No.

46:16.556 --> 46:18.079
Not in the way that you mean.

46:18.123 --> 46:20.212
In what way then?

46:20.255 --> 46:23.519
There are just people
that I talk to

46:23.563 --> 46:28.220
who think the way I think.

46:28.263 --> 46:33.660
About politics, about
literature, about music. I'm...

46:33.703 --> 46:37.316
I'm tired of shutting off
that part of myself.

46:37.359 --> 46:40.885
Don't make this
about politics if it's not.

46:43.104 --> 46:49.371
It is about politics.
And it is about beliefs.

46:50.720 --> 46:55.421
And our beliefs
are seriously not aligned.

46:55.464 --> 46:59.773
So, there's no room for love?

46:59.817 --> 47:02.994
I don't-- I don't know.
I mean...

47:06.649 --> 47:08.477
Yes, there's
always room for love.

47:08.521 --> 47:13.221
But that just feels
so inconsequential next to...

47:15.833 --> 47:18.705
Next to everything
that's going on.

47:26.321 --> 47:29.063
So, what then?

47:31.979 --> 47:33.807
Well, I mean...

47:38.246 --> 47:41.119
You go to D.C.
for your convention.

47:41.162 --> 47:43.077
I stay here.
And that's it.

47:44.687 --> 47:47.038
We barely live together now.

47:48.474 --> 47:52.652
So let's just continue
that way.

47:52.695 --> 47:54.480
And then, I mean, that's it.

48:09.756 --> 48:11.410
[shifter clunks]

48:11.453 --> 48:13.194
What are you doing?

48:17.938 --> 48:20.985
Getting an Uber. Goodbye.

